COMPONENT NAME: LKM Oracle to Oracle (DB Link) COMPONENT VERSION: 12.1.2.0.0 AUTHOR: Oracle COMPATIBILITY: ODI 12.1.2.0.0 or above
DESCRIPTION:
Oracle database link KM.
Create and load data into staging table
If this property is set to True the source data will be first loaded into staging table (C$_<name>) and then inserted into target.

Set this property to True if you want a database link to be created automatically when the mapping is run. This database link will be cleaned up at the end. Set this property to False if you want to reuse existing database link.

<?
String indexName = "$[tempIndexName]";
indexName = odiRef.getObjectName(indexName, "W");
if ("TRUE".equals("$[isConcurrent]")) {
  indexName = odiRef.getFormattedName(indexName + "%UNIQUE_STEP_TAG");
}
?>
create <%=odiRef.getTemporaryIndex("INDEX_TYPE_CLAUSE")%> index <?=indexName ?>
 on
$[stageTableAccessName]
<%=odiRef.getTemporaryIndexColList( "(", " [CX_COL_NAME] ", ", ", ")" )%>

<?
String indexName = "$[tempIndexName]";
indexName = odiRef.getObjectName(indexName, "W");
if ("TRUE".equals("$[isConcurrent]")) {
  indexName = odiRef.getFormattedName(indexName + "%UNIQUE_STEP_TAG");
}
?>
drop index <?=indexName ?>
LKM Oracle to Oracle (DB Link).Create staging (C$) table
LKM Oracle to Oracle (DB Link).Create temporary indexes on stage
LKM Oracle to Oracle (DB Link).Prepare: drop staging (C$) table
LKM Oracle to Oracle (DB Link).Drop staging (C$) table
LKM Oracle to Oracle (DB Link).Drop temporary indexes on stage
